# Example local layout file.
#
# This is the layout `D Restore` applies (also known as `display-restore.sh`).
# Goal: physical display is main at native resolution; any BetterDisplay virtual
# display used by `D Remote` is parked off-screen but kept enabled.
#
# Why off-screen instead of `enabled:false`: disabling a BetterDisplay virtual
# display works, but reconnecting it on the next `D Remote` run is unreliable.
# Parking it far off-screen lets each cycle reuse the same record cleanly.
#
# Replace this by running:
#   ../scripts/capture-layout.sh local
#
# The real command will be generated by `displayplacer list`.
displayplacer "id:your-display-id res:your-mode scaling:on origin:(0,0) degree:0" # PLACEHOLDER
